# Ralph Environment Variables
# Copy this file to $HOME/.ralph-env or scripts/ralph/.ralph-env and fill in your values.
# This file is NOT tracked by git.
#
# Ralph runs harnesses inside an isolated home directory under
# `scripts/ralph/runtime/home` by default so login state stays local to the
# project. Ralph seeds only minimal Codex/Pi config there; auth stays external.
# You can override that by setting `RALPH_HOME_DIR`.

# --- To use a consolidated provider (e.g., OpenRouter) ---
# Uncomment the following lines to route all harnesses through OpenRouter.
# This provides a single API key to access multiple model providers.
# export OPENAI_BASE_URL="https://openrouter.ai/api/v1"
# export OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-or-..."   # Your OpenRouter API key
# Claude Code is no longer a Ralph harness, so the Anthropic/OpenRouter
# Claude routing lines are intentionally left commented out for reference only.
# export ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL="https://openrouter.ai/api"
# export ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN="sk-or-..."
# export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=""   # Must be explicitly blank to avoid auth conflicts
# export ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_HAIKU_MODEL="~anthropic/claude-haiku-latest"
# export ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_SONNET_MODEL="~anthropic/claude-sonnet-latest"
# export ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_OPUS_MODEL="~anthropic/claude-opus-latest"

# --- To use native providers (automatic fallback on failure) ---
# Set the following *_NATIVE variables to enable one automatic fallback
# if the OpenRouter-backed first attempt fails (for example due to quota exhaustion).
# On fallback:
#   * OpenRouter base URL overrides are removed
#   * Native API keys are applied for the selected harness only
#   * Ralph does NOT fall back to stored harness OAuth/account auth
# For the framework, the native retry path uses OPENAI_API_KEY_NATIVE.
# If no matching native key is set, Ralph will fail after the OpenRouter attempt
# instead of trying account-based auth inside the framework.
#
# For Codex fallback to OpenAI native API:
#   export OPENAI_API_BASE_NATIVE="https://api.openai.com/v1"
#   export OPENAI_API_KEY_NATIVE="sk-..."   # Your OpenAI API key
#
# PI Agent-specific Zen settings are intentionally omitted from Ralph fallback.
# If you want to burn remaining OpenCode Zen credits, use PI standalone outside
# the framework with its own environment/session.
#
# --- Optional: Provider-specific overrides per harness ---
# If a harness requires different variables, set them here.
# export OPENCODE_BASE_URL="https://openrouter.ai/api/v1"
# export OPENCODE_API_KEY="sk-or-..."
# Example for PI Agent:
# export PI_BASE_URL="https://openrouter.ai/api/v1"
# export PI_API_KEY="sk-or-..."

# --- Fallback Note ---
# Ralph now uses a simple two-step policy:
#   1. Try the configured OpenRouter/provider route first
#   2. If that fails, retry once with the matching *_NATIVE API key
# There is no third framework-managed fallback to harness OAuth/account auth.
# To enable the second step, set the *_NATIVE variables as described above.
# If you do not set the *_NATIVE variables, no automatic fallback will occur.
# You can still use harness-specific OAuth/account login manually outside Ralph,
# but framework runs should rely on explicit env vars so behavior stays deterministic.
# 
# Examples:
#   # To fall back to native OpenAI API keys:
#   export OPENAI_API_KEY_NATIVE="sk-..."
#
#   # To use PI Zen outside Ralph:
#   # export PI_API_KEY_NATIVE="sk-op-..."
#   # export PI_API_BASE_NATIVE="https://opencode.ai/zen/v1/chat/completions"
#   # export PI_MODEL_NATIVE="opencode/nemotron-3-super-free"
#
#   # To disable native fallback for a harness:
#   # Leave the matching *_NATIVE variable unset
